      "date": "2016-05-31 10:50:54.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI think there is no strong technical requirement to mark every record with unique id. we just need to learn when record(s) are committed. I'd think it would be enough to tag a single record once a second (and assign commit cb as well), then all the records up to tagged one can be considered committed.",
